metadata.name: Brosser #248
metadata.description:
Exploring generative brush strokes to simulate real life paintings. 

- A selection of 19 different palettes
- 4 different drawing styles
- Randomized "color swap" between the primary and secondary colors in each palette

Several other factors determine the output of a piece, including angles, depth, brush length, and brush weight, among others.

metadata.name: A Pocket Full of Wonder #53
metadata.description:
"A Pocket Full of Wonder" invites you to embark on a journey where the boundaries between technology and art are blurred. 

Here, machine-generated images serve as a foundation for a vibrant and dynamic world of code-driven art. This union of artificial intelligence and creative coding evokes a sense of wonder and discovery, as each piece reveals the beauty that can be born from the interplay of technology and art. 

With "A Pocket Full of Wonder", we explore the limitless possibilities that emerge when we allow technology to augment and enhance our artistic visions.

metadata.name: Cosmic Poems #48
metadata.description:
Cosmic Poems is the fourth iteration of my work that explores the algorithmic space of typography. In this new piece, I expand on my initial inspirations of the early concrete poetry movement bringing in texts of my own. These short texts are taken from my extensive notes on the subject of artificial intelligence. Snippets of plausible pistes of reflection as well as lighter more tongue in cheek ideas make up the selection I have curated for the work. I hope that it may engage your attention with pleasure. 

Keys : ’s’ to save PNG

Program written by Mark Webster
Font design by simonrenaud.fr

mwebster.online
@motiondesign_01
